=TITLE Gnome::Gtk4::CellRendererSpinner
=head1 Description

Renders a spinning animation in a cell

B<Gnome::Gtk4::CellRendererSpinner> renders a spinning animation in a cell, very
similar to B<Gnome::Gtk4::Spinner>. It can often be used as an alternative
to a B<Gnome::Gtk4::CellRendererProgress> for displaying indefinite activity,
instead of actual progress.

To start the animation in a cell, set the B<Gnome::Gtk4::CellRendererSpinner>:active`
property to C<True> and increment the B<Gnome::Gtk4::CellRendererSpinner>:pulse` property
at regular intervals. The usual way to set the cell renderer properties
for each cell is to bind them to columns in your tree model using e.g.
gtk_tree_view_column_add_attribute().

